Nike Popoola Sigma Pensions has said it will examine the impact of COVID-19 on pension returns and employer-employee relationship in its forthcoming webinar. The company noted that the impact of the pandemic had become more evident in the cash flow of businesses and their ability to pay workers. It said in a statement that the webinar would expose staff to best practices in adapting to the new work environment and ways to offer better services to their clients. With human resource personnel and pension desk officers expected to attend, it said the webinar would be held in two sessions discussing the impact of COVID-19 on employer-employee relationships and pension returns. According to the statement, speakers expected at the webinar include the Employee Industrial Relations Manager, Shell Petroleum Development Company, Dr Steve Ojeh; the Head, Investment, Sigma Pensions, Mr Pabina Yinkere, and the Head, Business Development Division West, Sigma Pensions, Mrs Mabel George, who will moderate the sessions. It said Sigma Pensions had during the nationwide lockdown rigorously educated youths on the importance of having a pension plan. The statement said the youths expressed more interest in understanding the importance of having reliable pension fund administrators. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact:Â theeditor@punchng.com